Definition
-> Acts like a relative until a scroll limit is reached.
-> Then it becomes fixed.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.header {
 position: sticky;
 top: 0;
 background: yellow;
 padding: 10px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="header">Sticky Header</div>

<p style="height:2000px;">
Scroll down to see sticky effect.
</p>

</body>
</html>

📌 It sticks to top when scrolling.
